From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
Date: Sat, 14 Mar 2026 22:23:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] rockchip: board: Skip MAC address setup for Orange Pi 5
 Pro

The Orange Pi 5 Pro features a Motorcomm YT6801 PCIe Ethernet
controller with its own integrated eFuse for MAC address storage.
Auto-generating a MAC address from the Rockchip CPU ID would
override the NIC's unique hardware address.

This patch adds a check to skip the Rockchip MAC address setup
when running on an Orange Pi 5 Pro, allowing the Motorcomm driver
to use the address from its eFuse.

Signed-off-by: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
---
 arch/arm/mach-rockchip/board.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/board.c b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/board.c
index 2e6bb38b..0d68f621 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/board.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/board.c
@@ -335,6 +335,13 @@ int rockchip_setup_macaddr(void)
 	if (env_get("ethaddr"))
 		return 0;
 
+	/*
+	 * Orange Pi 5 Pro uses a PCIe-attached Motorcomm NIC with its own eFuse MAC.
+	 * Disable auto-generation to allow the ROM MAC to be used.
+	 */
+	if (of_machine_is_compatible("xunlong,orangepi-5-pro"))
+		return 0;
+
 	if (!cpuid) {
 		debug("%s: could not retrieve 'cpuid#'\n", __func__);
 		return -1;
-- 
